## Replace the tactical source section

The current plan’s tactical proposal payload is too broad. It includes:

```text
winning_single_cells
winning_pairs
terminal_equivalent_pairs
forced_block_cells
cover_pairs
open_four_cells
open_five_cells
overload_pairs
shared_pivot_pairs
hot_window_ids
impossible_to_cover
```

I would replace it with this for v1:

```text
TerminalTacticalSetV1 {
  status:
    quiet
    win_in_one
    must_block_loss_in_one
    loss_in_one_unblockable

  winning_single_cells
  winning_pairs
  terminal_equivalent_pairs

  opponent_win_requirements
  block_loss_pairs

  impossible_to_block
}
```

Definitions:

```text
winning_single_cells:
  legal cells that win immediately by completing a 5-window.

winning_pairs:
  legal unordered pairs that win this turn by completing a 4-window
  or by including a winning single cell.

terminal_equivalent_pairs:
  pairs whose outcome is identical because one member wins regardless
  of the second cell.

opponent_win_requirements:
  sets of cells the opponent could fill next turn to win.
  A 5-window requirement has size 1.
  A 4-window requirement has size 2.

block_loss_pairs:
  legal unordered pairs that intersect every opponent immediate
  win requirement.

impossible_to_block:
  true when no legal two-cell pair intersects every opponent immediate
  win requirement.
```

This keeps the exact terminal protection you need without trying to solve Hexo tactics in the candidate generator.

