## Update training target rules

Keep the existing rule:

```text
unsampled legal pair != negative pair
```

The current plan already says sparse positive rows do not imply omitted pairs have zero mass, and only admitted weak pairs or explicitly sampled negatives may contribute negative ranking signal. 

Add a terminal-specific rule:

```text
Terminal exact candidates receive protection in candidate admission,
but raw terminal protection must not pollute ordinary policy targets.

If own win-in-one exists:
  the improved target may collapse to terminal-winning candidates.
  terminal-equivalent pairs must be collapsed or tie-broken deterministically.

If opponent lose-in-one exists and own win-in-one does not:
  non-blocking pairs may be marked target-pruned or negative only if
  the terminal proof says they fail to block all opponent immediate wins.

If impossible_to_block is true:
  do not fabricate a winning defensive target.
  record tactical status and let value/search handle the losing state.
```

This is important because terminal exact logic should be allowed to override candidate selection, but not create noisy arbitrary pair preferences.

