## Updated plan thesis

I would rewrite the thesis like this:

```text
The mainline remains sampled joint-pair MCTS. The first implementation does
not attempt a rich tactical oracle. Instead, it builds the strongest possible
minimal pair candidate selector.

Tactical logic in v1 is terminal-only: exact win-in-one and exact lose-in-one.
All other pair discovery must come from model proposals, conditional proposals,
joint reranking, structured diversity, and search.

This makes the system easier to debug while preserving the no-compromise
semantic goal: after the opening, search acts on unordered pair macro-actions.
```

That is the update I would make. The plan becomes **more implementable and more testable** without becoming weaker. In fact, it becomes stronger because it identifies the real first bottleneck: **pair candidate selection quality**, not tactical-oracle sophistication.
